      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Drew Middleton (1913-1990) was a reporter for the Associated Press and the New York Times, noted for his combat reports as 
	  Foreign Correspondent for the Times during World War II, and his coverage and analysis of postwar Europe and the cold war.  He is author of more 
	  than a dozen books on military affairs, postwar diplomacy, and foreign policy.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Drew Middleton Papers</emph> consist of Memorabilia and Writings.</p><p><emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph>, donated separately, contains photographs, a clipping, and a postcard.</p><p><emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains manuscripts for four of Middleton's books.  There are 
		 three drafts of <emph render="italic">America's Stake in Asia</emph> (1967), two drafts and a set of galleys for 
		 <emph render="italic">The Atlantic Community</emph> (1965), one draft of 
		 <emph render="italic">Crisis in the West</emph> (1965), and one 
		 draft of <emph render="italic">Struggle for Germany</emph> (1949, his first book).  There are also two items of correspondence 
		 with his editors, one relating to each of the first two titles.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Writings are in alphabetical order by book title.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>The library has published editions of many of Middleton's books, including <emph render="italic">Our Share of Night : A Personal 
		 Narrative of the War Years</emph>.  Please refer to &summitref; to locate these items.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
      
